to\": 6921}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6936, \"to\": 6948}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 6959, \"to\": 6967}, {\"ngram\": \"the looks\", \"from\": 6985, \"to\": 6994}, {\"ngram\": \"the greater publicity boon\", \"from\": 7006, \"to\": 7032}, {\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 7039, \"to\": 7052}, {\"ngram\": \"certain sports\", \"from\": 7066, \"to\": 7080}, {\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 7085, \"to\": 7092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stranger and equally as wonderful are Flavor Flav's enthusiastic shout-outs to the USA women's water polo Olympic team, part of a five-year sponsorship deal casting him as its official hype man as well as the booster for the men's national teams.\", \"from\": 7095, \"to\": 7341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7135, \"end\": 7146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flavor_Flav\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0006636597662998e-79, \"text\": \"Flavor Flav\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flavor_Flav\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flavor_Flav\"}, {\"begin\": 7180, \"end\": 7183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.549030868689707e-17, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a five-year sponsorship deal\", \"from\": 7223, \"to\": 7251}, {\"ngram\": \"its official hype man\", \"from\": 7267, \"to\": 7288}, {\"ngram\": \"the booster\", \"from\": 7300, \"to\": 7311}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's national teams\", \"from\": 7316, \"to\": 7340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Flav, born William Jonathan Drayton Jr., served that role in the seminal hip-hop group Public Enemy before emerging as a reality star in the aughts via Season 3 of \\\"The Surreal Life,\\\" from which spun off \\\"Strange Love,\\\" where he roma